06/01/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Interior Ministry Chief Secretary General Boyko Borisov and Cyprus Police Chief Tassos Panayiotou met on Monday (5 January) to discuss joint efforts against terrorism and organised crime. 
The top police officials reviewed implementation of the bilateral co-operation agreement signed last month, as well as measures against trans-border crime, terrorism, illegal migration, and human and drug trafficking.
In other news, President Georgi Parvanov spoke by phone Monday with Polish counterpart Aleksander Kwasniewski, discussing Bulgarian casualties in Iraq, as well as NATO and EU integration issues. 
(Trud, 24 Chassa - 06/01/04; BTA, BNT, Nova TV, PAP - 05/01/04)
